This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with evaluating the impact of user mobility on 5G small cell networks. Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper considers human tendency and clustering behaviors, cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper derives probabilities for evaluating user mobility performance, cs.MM (Multimedia) as small cell networks are often used for multimedia applications, and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as security is an important aspect of 5G networks.
